Package: seafile-server
Architecture: any
Pre-Depends: ${misc:Pre-Depends},
Depends: python3-pymysql,
         redis-server | memcached,
         seafile-server-data (= ${source:Version}),
         ${misc:Depends},
         ${python3:Depends},
         ${shlibs:Depends},
Suggests: default-mysql-server | virtual-mysql-server,
Built-Using: ${misc:Built-Using},
Description: Open source cloud storage and file sync server
 Seafile is a self-hosted file sync and share solution with high performance
 and reliability. It offers file syncing across devices, selective sync,
 client-side and server-side encryption, and team collaboration features.
 .
 This package contains the complete Seafile Community Edition server: the
 storage and sync daemons (seaf-server, the go file server and notification
 server), the Seahub web frontend together with its background task server
 (seafevents) and WebDAV server (seafdav), and the database migration tooling.
 Seahub's Python dependencies ship as a bundled virtualenv resolved with uv at
 build time.

Package: seafile-server-data
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
Description: Open source cloud storage and file sync server - application data
 Seafile is a self-hosted file sync and share solution with high performance
 and reliability. It offers file syncing across devices, selective sync,
 client-side and server-side encryption, and team collaboration features.
 .
 This package contains the architecture-independent parts of the Seahub web
 frontend: the Django application with its prebuilt frontend assets and the
 bundled seafevents and seafdav components.

Package: seafile-fuse
Architecture: any
Depends: fuse3,
         seafile-server (= ${binary:Version}),
         ${misc:Depends},
         ${shlibs:Depends},
Description: Open source cloud storage and file sync - FUSE filesystem
 Seafile is a self-hosted file sync and share solution with high performance
 and reliability. It offers file syncing across devices, selective sync,
 client-side and server-side encryption, and team collaboration features.
 .
 This package contains seaf-fuse, a read-only FUSE filesystem that presents
 the libraries in a Seafile object store as regular directories and files.
